
Module 'math' contains utilities that execute various common
math functions to help determine the jobs to be queued.  

-------------------------------------------------------------------
REQUIREMENTS
-------------------------------------------------------------------

Only standard Linux utilities are used by the math module.
    
-------------------------------------------------------------------
integer.q
-------------------------------------------------------------------

Demand that a variable be an integer, otherwise throw an error at 
submission time.

Required variables:
$VALUE     The value to test. Test multiple values using a list 
           invocation.
    
Example:
$VALUES    55 0 6.3
invoke math/integer.q $VALUE $VALUES

-------------------------------------------------------------------
non_zero.q
-------------------------------------------------------------------

Demand that a variable not be zero, otherwise throw an error at 
submission time.

Required variables:
$VALUE     The value to test. Test multiple values using a list 
           invocation.
    
Example:
$VALUES    55 0 6.3
invoke math/non_zero.q $VALUE $VALUES



